                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d880">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12963.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>132. Carranza yesterday notified the Governors of States and other Mexican
                    authorities that he had assumed the Executive Power but without stating in what
                    capacity. No notice has been given to Diplomatic Corps, whose existence here
                    they seem inclined to ignore, considering foreign representatives merely as
                    private persons. Were it not for my good offices, British Minister would have
                    received his passports instead of going voluntarily tomorrow. They have also
                    dismissed all Mexican Government secretaries and consuls in all foreign
                    countries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
